[quote=“DannyIsSoPro, post:12, topic:449281”]Goodddd dammnittt lol. Sorry but I don’t know how many times I must tell people Utorrent does not forward ports! Sorry boutz datss… LOL.
Anyways, if you just want to connect to the server by yourself, there is no need to forward any ports, and there is no need to use a no-ip. If you’re trying connect yourself, just go into the client and change all the IP’s to 127.0.0.1, localhost, or 0.0.0.0
You only change those IP’s to your no-ip when you are distributing your client to your friends/the public.
I hope I cleared things up. :3[/quote]

Anyways, if you just want to connect to the server by yourself, there is no need to forward any ports, and there is no need to use a no-ip. If you’re trying connect yourself, just go into the client and change all the IP’s to 127.0.0.1, localhost, or 0.0.0.0
